        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 7 at 5:48AM CDT by NWS Hastings NE</headline>
        <description>At 547 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Miller, or 26 miles northeast of Lexington, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northwestern
Buffalo and southwestern Sherman Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
